We urge India to stop bloodbath in Kashmir: Nawaz Sharif.
Upping the ante, Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif today said Kashmir is the "core dispute" between India and Pakistan and the dream of peace and prosperity of the people of the region will remain elusive without resolving the issue. Describing Kashmir issue is the "unfinished agenda of partition and the oldest disputes in the UN Security Council, Sharif said "for the last seven decades India has denied the people of Kashmir the right to self-determination promised to them by the international community through numerous UN Security Council resolutions". He was speaking on the occasion of Kashmir Solidarity Day.Also read: Pak minister: Hope assembly elections in India help resume talks